|  |  |  |pl|  |  |  |  
|  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  
|  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  
|  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  
|  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  
|The pawn may capture either the rook or the knight, but not the bishop, which blocks the pawn from moving directly forward.
}}
{{Chess diagram
